OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FThe regiment was surrounded on three
OL,8,Fsides by German troops and within days
OL,9,Fmore than 320 of them were killed.
OL,11,FThe service took place in the French
OL,12,Ftown of Masnieres, just outside
OL,13,FCambrai, where the regiment suffered
OL,14,Fits heaviest losses.
OL,16,FMasnieres residents paid tribute to
OL,17,Fthe Guernseymen who protected their
OL,18,Ftown, with one saying: "In a way to
OL,19,Fremember about those who came here to
OL,20,Fdefend us."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/10
