OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FAnother explains: "I think it's
OL,8,Fimportant not to forget all the
OL,9,Fsoldiers that have fallen for us here."
OL,11,FDignitaries from Guernsey were also in
OL,12,Fattendance, including the Bailiff of
OL,13,FGuernsey and Lieutenant Governor Lt.
OL,14,FGen. Richard Cripwell - the first time
OL,15,Fthey've attended the service at the
OL,16,Fsame time.
