OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FLt. Gen. Cripwell says: "It really was
OL,8,Fvery special to see so many people out
OL,9,Fon a cold day - not as cold as it was
OL,10,Fback in 1917, but particularly to hear
OL,11,Fthe children singing our national
OL,12,Fanthem and the French national anthem
OL,13,Fso beautifully.
OL,15,F"And (they are) so clearly engaged in
OL,16,Fwhat was going on."
OL,18,FWho were the Royal Guernsey Light
OL,19,FInfantry?
