OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FThe Royal Guernsey Light Infantry was
OL,8,Fan infantry regiment of the British
OL,9,FArmy formed from the Royal Guernsey
OL,10,FMilitia in 1916 to serve in World War
OL,11,FI.
OL,13,FThey fought the Battle of Cambrai,
OL,14,Fwhere the RGLI's role was to go
OL,15,Fthrough the Hindenburg Line after the
OL,16,Ffirst wave and take 'Nine Wood' to the
OL,17,Fnorth of Marcoing.
OL,19,FThis went according to plan, with few
OL,20,Fcasualties and they then moved on to
OL,21,Fthe front line at Masnieres.
