OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FOn 2 December 1917, the Guernseymen
OL,8,Ffound themselves defending the small
OL,9,Ftown of Les Rues Vertes against a huge
OL,10,Fand determined German counter-attacks.
OL,12,FThe RGLI were the only British
OL,13,Fregiment to hold the line, whilst
OL,14,Fother Allied troops around them were
OL,15,Fforced to withdraw. The RGLI were
OL,16,Ffundamental in preventing the German
OL,17,Fcounter-offensive from being
OL,18,Fsuccessful.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/10
