OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FTerry Coule's grandfather was one of
OL,8,Fthe hundreds of Guerseymen who fought
OL,9,Fin the RGLI, who also lost his 21-year-
OL,10,Fold brother in the regiment.
OL,12,FHe explains: "After the fighting, my
OL,13,Fgrandfather wrote to his Mother and
OL,14,Fsaid 'I can't find babe', and his
OL,15,Fyounger brother had been killed in the
OL,16,Fattack ` but they couldn't find his
OL,17,Fbody.
OL,19,F"It was never recovered, so he was
OL,20,Fjust posted as missing."
