OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FThe sacrifice of the Guernsey soldiers
OL,8,Fmeant that the RGLI entered 1918 with
OL,9,F50% of the men being non-Guernsey born.
OL,11,FDean of Guernsey, the Very Reverend
OL,12,FTim Barker, says: "This was perhaps
OL,13,Fone of the most significant times in
OL,14,FGuernsey's history.
OL,16,F"Of course, the occupation was a
OL,17,Ftremendously important part of our
OL,18,Fhistory, but perhaps that's eclipsed
OL,19,Fin some ways the memory of just how
OL,20,Fdevastating the events of 1917 were
OL,21,Ffor the islands."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/10
