OL,3,CRemembering the 327 Guernseymen who
OL,4,Clost their lives in the Battle of
OL,5,CCambrai
OL,7,FLt Col Colin Vaudin of The RGLI
OL,8,FCharitable Trust adds: "Husbands;
OL,9,Ffathers; it was a tragedy for Guernsey
OL,10,Fbut also something we should be
OL,11,Fimmensely proud of that the men of
OL,12,FGuernsey stood here and fought
OL,13,Funtrained against the might of the
OL,14,FGerman Army.
OL,16,F"I'm incredibly proud of them but
OL,17,Fincredibly sorry for the sacrifice
OL,18,Fthey made."
